comments.content:
Thanks everyone for the help.

@hartmannsgruber: I will certainly try to get a hold of Huda Smitshuijzen Abifares' book

@Ken Lunde: I will discuss readability in relation to different types of media/circumstances. E.g.: Low resolution screens and highway signs demand a simpler letterform; a sans...

@Hrant: thanks for the very interesting examples. I love the solution of a slightly slanted, semi-serif roman as a companion to the armenian font. Very nice to see the latin being moddeled after the Armenian, instead of the (usual) other way around.

The role of serifs in relation to multi-script systems is indeed the interessanting angle. Unfortunatly I don't speak/read any language in a non-Latin script. So I won't be able to do extensive research and I will have to rely on other people since I can't tell wether a certain script has been latinized and if the result looks odd

Thanks again  
Wouter
